<subSubSection id="C33311E1FFE57F0C99F7E0F7D68BFC5A" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8B96426AFFE57F0C99F7E0F7D68BFC5A" blockId="32.[151,1436,796,1279]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">
<emphasis id="B95D9E78FFE57F0C99F7E0F7D51CFC08" bold="true" box="[198,526,904,930]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Distribution and ecology:</emphasis>
—Known only from humid forest edges at 
<quantity id="4CD1EF8FFFE57F0C9D1DE0F6D3C6FC09" box="[1068,1236,905,931]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.6" metricValueMax="2.0" metricValueMin="1.2" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" unit="m" value="1600.0" valueMax="2000.0" valueMin="1200.0">1200–2000 m</quantity>
in 
<collectingRegion id="49ED8C88FFE57F0C9C32E0F6D67AFC60" country="Cuba" name="Santiago de Cuba" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Provincia de Santiago de Cuba</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F33E02FAFFE57F0C9842E0CFD6A6FC60" box="[371,436,944,970]" name="Cuba" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Cuba</collectingCountry>
, but to be expected where the parental taxa co-occur, e.g., in 
<collectingCountry id="F33E02FAFFE57F0C9D4DE0CFD3CAFC60" box="[1148,1240,944,970]" name="Mexico" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Mexico</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F33E02FAFFE57F0C9DD5E0CFD274FC60" box="[1252,1382,944,970]" name="Guatemala" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Guatemala</collectingCountry>
, and 
<collectingCountry id="F33E02FAFFE57F0C99A6E0A9D7E7FC5A" box="[151,245,982,1008]" name="Jamaica" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Jamaica</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFB83F9BFFE57F0C9835E0A9D69EFC5A" author="Duek, J. J." box="[260,396,982,1008]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" pagination="74 - 80" refId="ref30989" refString="Duek, J. J. (1974). A newly recognized Gleichenia hybrid from Cuba. American Fern Journal 64: 74 - 80." type="journal article" year="1974">Duek 1974</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C33311E1FFE57F0C99F7E082D7EFFB55" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B96426AFFE57F0C99F7E082D7EFFB55" blockId="32.[151,1436,796,1279]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">
<emphasis id="B95D9E78FFE57F0C99F7E082D607FBBD" bold="true" box="[198,277,1021,1047]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Notes:</emphasis>
—This taxon was originally described by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB83F9BFFE57F0C9A20E082D4D9FBBD" author="Maxon, W. R." box="[785,971,1021,1047]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" pagination="437 - 443" refId="ref32578" refString="Maxon, W. R. (1922 b) Ferns new to the Cuban flora. Journal of the Washington Academy of Sciences 12: 437 - 443." type="journal article" year="1922">Maxon (1922b)</bibRefCitation>
as a distinct species, but 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB83F9BFFE57F0C9C35E082D289FBBD" author="Duek, J. J." box="[1284,1435,1021,1047]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" pagination="74 - 80" refId="ref30989" refString="Duek, J. J. (1974). A newly recognized Gleichenia hybrid from Cuba. American Fern Journal 64: 74 - 80." type="journal article" year="1974">Duek (1974)</bibRefCitation>
recognized that all specimens appeared to be sterile, with few sporangia, and malformed spores. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB83F9BFFE57F0C9C36E75BD289FB94" author="Duek, J. J." box="[1287,1435,1060,1086]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" pagination="74 - 80" refId="ref30989" refString="Duek, J. J. (1974). A newly recognized Gleichenia hybrid from Cuba. American Fern Journal 64: 74 - 80." type="journal article" year="1974">Duek (1974)</bibRefCitation>
postulated that the parental species were 
<taxonomicName id="4C2939E9FFE57F0C9BA0E734D42FFBCE" authorityName="J. Gonzales" authorityYear="2011" baseAuthorityName="Desv." box="[657,829,1099,1124]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Gleicheniaceae" genus="Sticherus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gleicheniales" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ferrugineus">
<emphasis id="B95D9E78FFE57F0C9BA0E734D42FFBCE" box="[657,829,1099,1124]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">S. ferrugineus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(called 
<taxonomicName id="4C2939E9FFE57F0C9A93E734D307FBCE" authorityName="Ching" authorityYear="1940" baseAuthorityName="Willd." box="[930,1045,1099,1124]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Gleicheniaceae" genus="Sticherus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gleicheniales" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="bifidus">
<emphasis id="B95D9E78FFE57F0C9A93E734D307FBCE" box="[930,1045,1099,1124]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">S. bifidus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by Duek) and 
<taxonomicName id="4C2939E9FFE57F0C9DFFE734D25DFBCE" authorityName="Ching" authorityYear="1940" baseAuthorityName="L." box="[1230,1359,1099,1124]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Gleicheniaceae" genus="Sticherus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gleicheniales" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="furcatus">
<emphasis id="B95D9E78FFE57F0C9DFFE734D25DFBCE" box="[1230,1359,1099,1124]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">S. furcatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(as 
<taxonomicName id="4C2939E9FFE57F0C9CB4E734D610FB20" authorityName="Copeland" authorityYear="1947" baseAuthorityName="W. Schaffn. ex E. Fourn." class="Polypodiopsida" family="Gleicheniaceae" genus="Sticherus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gleicheniales" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="palmatus">
<emphasis id="B95D9E78FFE57F0C9CB4E734D610FB20" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">S. palmatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). It is more probable that the parental taxa are actually 
<taxonomicName id="4C2939E9FFE57F0C9AA3E70ED33AFB20" authorityName="J. Gonzales" authorityYear="2011" box="[914,1064,1137,1162]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Gleicheniaceae" genus="Sticherus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gleicheniales" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="antillensis">
<emphasis id="B95D9E78FFE57F0C9AA3E70ED33AFB20" box="[914,1064,1137,1162]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">S. antillensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C2939E9FFE57F0C9D52E70ED3F2FB20" authorityName="Ching" authorityYear="1940" baseAuthorityName="L." box="[1123,1248,1137,1162]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Gleicheniaceae" genus="Sticherus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gleicheniales" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="furcatus">
<emphasis id="B95D9E78FFE57F0C9D52E70ED3F2FB20" box="[1123,1248,1137,1162]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">S. furcatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
because its bud scales are large, bicolorous, basally rigid and marginally translucent, and thus very similar to those of 
<taxonomicName id="4C2939E9FFE57F0C9CB4E7E7D61DFB72" authorityName="J. Gonzales" authorityYear="2011" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Gleicheniaceae" genus="Sticherus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gleicheniales" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="antillensis">
<emphasis id="B95D9E78FFE57F0C9CB4E7E7D61DFB72" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">S. antillensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, whereas the glabrous abaxial segments, and lanceolate abaxial branch scales are reminiscent of 
<taxonomicName id="4C2939E9FFE57F0C9CB7E7C0D7E4FB54" authorityName="Ching" authorityYear="1940" baseAuthorityName="L." class="Polypodiopsida" family="Gleicheniaceae" genus="Sticherus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gleicheniales" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="furcatus">
<emphasis id="B95D9E78FFE57F0C9CB7E7C0D7E4FB54" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">S. furcatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
